<br>
Keep in mind also that you won't always have an enchanter around and the difference from 22% haste to 36% haste is HUGE.  Try it one day, run some logs, you dps numbers will be drastically different.<br>
<br>
Slot also largely effects cost.  Back slot haste items are generally desired over belt slot haste for certain classes depending on other gear available.<br>
<br>
CoF also has very low weight, making it desirable for monks.<br>
<br>
It's also one of the few very high end tradable haste items.<br>
<br>
It's worth more than the CotCW because HP own Mana for most melee classes.<br>
<br>
It's considered by a lot of people to be a &quot;terminal&quot; item.  Meaning, you will wear it pretty much until the end of time.  Unless you are in a guild farming NToV or Yelinak, you are not going to see a higher haste item outside a rogue epic or a Cowel of Mortality.  However, a head slot is not generally considered a good place to wear a haste item, it's more of an AC slot.<br>
<br>
90k really isn't THAT much money.  Anyone who put their mind to it could raise 90k in a month or 2.  CoF's drop at what rate?  Twice a week (give or take)?  That's 12 to 16 coming into the economy in the time it takes you to raise the cash.  With a very high demand (a lot of it for twinks) I think the price is fairly reasonable.  Also, most people that win them are not allowed to sell them.  At any given time there are maybe 2 or 3 CoF's on the open market on ARo.<br>
<br>
Hope this helps.<br>
<br>
Chopa<br>
