Answer:  Because people are willing to pay that much for them. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/utalerenbloodsong.showPublicProfile?language=EN>talerenbloodsong</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(11/16/01 9:43:22 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Cloak of Flames - 90K - Why?</span><hr size=1>      You guys are missing the point with the new bard haste that stacks, its not making ALL bard hastes stack.  No your 45% bard haste isn't gonna stack, it's going to be one particular song that isn't going to have a huge haste bonus that will stack.  You will still need shissar and a good haste item to get the most effect out of the new bard haste cap. Also on a raid not every group has a bard, so the melee's without a bard still need good haste.  When you grind you dont generally have a bard and an enchanter, so in that case a good haste would still be needed.  It is not going to be an every day occurence where people are simply going to have access to an enchanter and have a bard in their group.<br>
     Now to the Cloak of Flames and it's value reference:  I wouldn't call it rare anymore, but it (and rbb) are generally the best PURCHASABLE haste item.  There is still alot of coins floating around the game and people are willing to pay that for the best haste item they can buy.  It has very nice stats, gives hp, and gives good fire resist too.  It would be a very valuable cloak even without the haste (probably 10-15k on this server).  Is 36% haste worth 75k?  It sure is if you don't have it and you are a melee class.<br>
     People say that nothing in the game is worth 90k, ok don't buy it.  But what good does a bunch of silver coins sitting in people's banks do them?  The only people I see here saying it is not worth 90k are the ones that don't have 90k and aren't willing to put in the time to earn it.<br>
